Paper: hep-th/0110226

Date: 2001-10-24

Title: Imprints of Short Distance Physics On Inflationary Cosmology

Authors: Richard Easther, Brian R. Greene, William H. Kinney and Gary Shiu

Comments: Revtex 4, 3 eps figs, 4 pages

We analyze the impact of certain modifications to short distance physics onthe inflationary perturbation spectrum. For the specific case of power-lawinflation, we find distinctive -- and possibly observable -- effects on thespectrum of density perturbations.